TopicTitle: What did you name your first rocket?

Articles.Content:
Owlet I

Yeah, big mystery what flag I chose.

Is it normal to remember our first rocket? I have no clue what my first rocket was named.

I don't have to remember the names, I still have the craft files. ;-)

"KSTR - I" which stands for "Kerbin Suborbital Test Rocket - Mark 1"

It actually made a "suborbital" hop of about 1500 Ap, and half-crash-landed, destroying the booster, but still... Success!

Untitled Space Craft

^^^^^^^

ASES (Avionics, Space Exploration and Science) F01. Right now I'm working on the F04 series of rockets. It seems that the letter 'F' fits rather well with rockets, see the legendary F1 engine and Space X's Falcon series of rockets for example. I also use suffixes, e.g. 'F03-a' means it's an aspargus staged rocket, 'F03-al' denotes an aspargus staged rocket featuring a lander and so on.

X1

/extra chars added to placate the bot
The Vega. Lifted a satellite into orbit.
It was either Kerbal 11 or Untitled Space Craft.
Knowing they were going to crash and burn, I named my first few rockets after ex-girlfriends.

I don't recall. It may have been "Icarus I", or maybe "Untitled Space Craft".

For my newest save, it was Nova I.

Mun-1

It got there...it just got to the ground at 500m/s
Seriously "Hold My Beer and Watch This Mk. 1" I can send the craft file if you like.
